Let me confirm something first.

00:29:12.175 --> 00:29:13.175
About what?

00:29:14.745 --> 00:29:16.215
What was Professor Han's part in this?

00:29:16.915 --> 00:29:17.955
Professor Han?

00:29:20.555 --> 00:29:21.885
I reached out to him myself.

00:29:23.895 --> 00:29:26.425
- What's your relationship with him?
- What do you mean, relationship?

00:29:26.925 --> 00:29:28.265
He was just my doctor.

00:29:29.365 --> 00:29:32.065
If Professor Han knew about
your condition from the start,

00:29:33.535 --> 00:29:34.665
then he must have known about the cure...

00:29:35.465 --> 00:29:36.665
as well.

00:29:37.105 --> 00:29:38.575
What are you talking about?
He didn't know.

00:29:39.675 --> 00:29:44.375
And stop trying to connect the two of us.
He and I are nothing alike.

00:29:45.545 --> 00:29:46.545
How so?

00:29:47.615 --> 00:29:51.515
I'm telling you. That man has no idea
how to make the cure.

00:29:53.155 --> 00:29:55.055
He spent his whole life
trying to develop a cure,

00:29:55.125 --> 00:29:58.555
but he failed. Of course
I'm different from a loser like him.

00:29:59.695 --> 00:30:03.695
He visited me before and kept asking
how I developed the cure.

00:30:04.195 --> 00:30:06.265
It was so annoying.

00:30:07.305 --> 00:30:10.135
Still, I guess I can see why
someone like him would do that.

00:30:11.235 --> 00:30:14.245
- Is that all?
- What'd you expect? That we were dating?

00:30:18.215 --> 00:30:21.615
Do you happen to know where
Professor Han might be staying?

00:30:23.285 --> 00:30:24.555
Why? Can't you reach him?

00:30:24.815 --> 00:30:27.225
No, I can't get ahold of him.
For our case,

00:30:27.825 --> 00:30:30.455
he's the only witness
who can testify about you.

00:30:32.055 --> 00:30:34.225
Let's not worry about Professor Han...

00:30:35.025 --> 00:30:36.725
and just focus on
the medical demonstration.

00:30:37.695 --> 00:30:39.195
We're so close to the finish line.

00:30:39.765 --> 00:30:41.235
We need to see this demonstration
through to the end.

00:30:41.635 --> 00:30:45.205
Instead of looking for Professor Han,
go buy a gift for Min Seo.

00:31:06.925 --> 00:31:09.595
You pulled off the medical demonstration
after all.

00:31:10.665 --> 00:31:11.695
Congratulations.

00:31:14.365 --> 00:31:15.735
You know, it's amazing...

00:31:16.435 --> 00:31:17.535
how you never change.

00:31:19.235 --> 00:31:21.105
Then and now, whenever you lie,

00:31:21.805 --> 00:31:23.805
the corner of your mouth
curls up slightly.

00:31:24.675 --> 00:31:25.815
When do I do that?

00:31:26.475 --> 00:31:29.645
And when you're embarrassed,
you always look away.

00:31:30.245 --> 00:31:31.285
Some things never change.

00:31:33.085 --> 00:31:36.055
Why on earth do you have to go through
with this medical demonstration?

00:31:37.225 --> 00:31:38.295
To prove his motive.

00:31:38.855 --> 00:31:40.055
But he already confessed.

00:31:40.795 --> 00:31:44.265
If his confession were enough,
then his sentence should be reconsidered.

00:31:45.535 --> 00:31:46.965
Is that really why you're doing this?

00:31:47.835 --> 00:31:49.635
Just to get his sentence reduced?

00:31:49.935 --> 00:31:51.405
Why? Does that make you nervous?

00:31:52.105 --> 00:31:54.475
You're the one who's nervous, not me.

00:31:55.645 --> 00:31:57.615
Why did you hide
what's happening with Min Seo?

00:31:58.075 --> 00:32:01.385
Hiding something
and not saying anything are different.

00:32:01.885 --> 00:32:02.885
Besides,

00:32:03.215 --> 00:32:05.985
why would you need to know about
the opposing counsel's personal life?

00:32:08.555 --> 00:32:09.555
Stay out of it.

00:32:10.485 --> 00:32:12.155
So is that why,
back at the training institute,

00:32:13.325 --> 00:32:16.965
you'd get drunk and keep telling me
that, "People come before the law,"

00:32:17.025 --> 00:32:18.565
and stay up all night repeating yourself?

00:32:20.195 --> 00:32:21.205
Han Jun.

00:32:22.105 --> 00:32:23.605
Even now, at the Judicial Research
and Training Institute,

00:32:24.135 --> 00:32:26.205
you're still held up as a model example.

00:32:28.405 --> 00:32:29.575
Well, I guess it's about time...

00:32:30.145 --> 00:32:31.445
for that to change, then.

00:32:31.515 --> 00:32:35.385
What happened to the prosecutor who always
put away every scumbag he could find?

00:32:35.445 --> 00:32:38.255
I'm simply doing the best I can
for my client.

00:32:38.315 --> 00:32:39.985
But this is Lee Woo Gyeom
we're talking about.

00:32:41.225 --> 00:32:43.285
You're really going to accept help
from a murderer like him?

00:32:43.855 --> 00:32:46.795
Since when have you ever cared
who the defendant is?

00:32:47.595 --> 00:32:50.265
You just need a high-profile case
to make a name for yourself.

00:32:51.435 --> 00:32:52.635
And what's wrong with that?

00:32:52.635 --> 00:32:54.305
Don't use Lee Woo Gyeom's
death sentence...

00:32:55.965 --> 00:32:58.405
as a stepping stone for your career.

00:32:59.305 --> 00:33:02.475
You can reach your goals
without Lee Woo Gyeom, but I...

00:33:03.905 --> 00:33:05.815
I need him right now.

00:33:06.715 --> 00:33:10.345
You think Lee Woo Gyeom
is really going to cure Min Seo?

00:33:10.855 --> 00:33:12.285
What if he's lying?

00:33:12.815 --> 00:33:14.885
There's no guarantee
the treatment will even work.

00:33:16.085 --> 00:33:19.125
That's why I'm saying we should find
a legitimate way to do this.

00:33:19.825 --> 00:33:21.725
I'll help in any way I can.

00:33:22.095 --> 00:33:25.395
If you need money for the treatment...
I know you won't like this, but...

00:33:25.465 --> 00:33:26.465
Yi Yeon.

00:33:30.805 --> 00:33:32.005
That's enough.

00:33:36.545 --> 00:33:37.715
I'll see you in court.

00:33:38.145 --> 00:33:40.715
You know this is wrong.

00:33:41.345 --> 00:33:43.715
Why are you giving
a guy like that a chance?

00:33:44.885 --> 00:33:48.125
- Let me help you get the treatment.
- That's not what this is about, darn it!

00:33:49.585 --> 00:33:51.095
If it was something
a treatment could solve,

00:33:51.755 --> 00:33:53.125
I wouldn't have gone this far.

00:33:54.295 --> 00:33:56.095
I look at that jerk, Lee Woo Gyeom,

00:33:57.495 --> 00:33:59.335
and I second-guess myself
hundreds of times a day.

00:34:00.395 --> 00:34:03.035
I told myself I'd rather die
than defend that monster.

00:34:05.175 --> 00:34:06.735
But then... My daughter, Min Seo...

00:34:08.405 --> 00:34:09.845
is really dying.

00:34:11.515 --> 00:34:13.975
They said she could die any second,
not tomorrow, but right now.

00:34:15.615 --> 00:34:17.285
That was a wake-up call for me.

00:34:18.715 --> 00:34:20.855
I realized what I've been living
for all this time.

00:34:23.955 --> 00:34:24.955
I...

00:34:26.095 --> 00:34:28.095
don't care about anything else
in this world...

00:34:28.865 --> 00:34:30.425
except for getting my Min Seo treated.

00:34:31.395 --> 00:34:32.935
Even if this is the wrong choice,

00:34:34.065 --> 00:34:36.005
I would make it all over again.

00:34:37.405 --> 00:34:38.405
Understand?

00:34:42.905 --> 00:34:43.905
Han Jun...

00:34:52.255 --> 00:34:53.255
Yi Yeon.

00:34:56.055 --> 00:34:58.195
Then all you have to do
is beat me in court.

00:35:08.065 --> 00:35:09.065
To be honest,

00:35:12.405 --> 00:35:14.445
I'd rather you win.

